briefdescription.para: Popup the window (this will show it too).

detaileddescription.para: If winFocus is non-NULL, it will be kept focused while this window is shown, otherwise this window itself will receive focus. In any case, the popup will disappear automatically if it loses focus because of a user action.

briefdescription.para: Called when a mouse is pressed while the popup is shown.

detaileddescription.para: Return true from here to prevent its normal processing by the popup (which consists in dismissing it if the mouse is clicked outside it).

briefdescription.para: This is called when the popup is disappeared because of anything else but direct call to Dismiss().
A wxPopupWindow which disappears automatically when the user clicks mouse outside it or if it loses focus in any other way.

detaileddescription.para: This window can be useful for implementing custom combobox-like controls for example.
